Entries.Name: EventTopics
Docs: Mapping between a topic (represented by T::Hash) and a vector of indexes
of events in the `<Events<T>>` list.
All topic vectors have deterministic storage locations depending on the topic. This
allows light-clients to leverage the changes trie storage tracking mechanism and
in case of changes fetch the list of events of interest.
The value has the type `(BlockNumberFor<T>, EventIndex)` because if we used only just
the `EventIndex` then in case if the topic has the same contents on the next block
no notification will be triggered thus the event might be lost.

Entries.Name: Account
Docs: The Balances pallet example of storing the balance of an account.
# Example
```nocompile
impl pallet_balances::Config for Runtime {
type AccountStore = StorageMapShim<Self::Account<Runtime>, frame_system::Provider<Runtime>, AccountId, Self::AccountData<Balance>>
You can also store the balance of an account in the `System` pallet.
# Example
```nocompile
impl pallet_balances::Config for Runtime {
type AccountStore = System
But this comes with tradeoffs, storing account balances in the system pallet stores
`frame_system` data alongside the account data contrary to storing account balances in the
`Balances` pallet, which uses a `StorageMap` to store balances data only.
NOTE: This is only used in the case that this pallet is used to store balances.

Constants.Name: OperationalFeeMultiplier
Docs: A fee mulitplier for `Operational` extrinsics to compute "virtual tip" to boost their
`priority`
This value is multipled by the `final_fee` to obtain a "virtual tip" that is later
added to a tip component in regular `priority` calculations.
It means that a `Normal` transaction can front-run a similarly-sized `Operational`
extrinsic (with no tip), by including a tip value greater than the virtual tip.
```rust,ignore
// For `Normal`
let priority = priority_calc(tip);
// For `Operational`
let virtual_tip = (inclusion_fee + tip) * OperationalFeeMultiplier;
let priority = priority_calc(tip + virtual_tip);
Note that since we use `final_fee` the multiplier applies also to the regular `tip`
sent with the transaction. So, not only does the transaction get a priority bump based
on the `inclusion_fee`, but we also amplify the impact of tips applied to `Operational`
transactions.

- `LastTabledWasExternal` is `false`; or
- `PublicProps` is empty.

Entries.Name: Blacklist
Docs: A record of who vetoed what. Maps proposal hash to a possible existent block number
(until when it may not be resubmitted) and who vetoed it.

Entries.Name: Cancellations
Docs: Record of all proposals that have been subject to emergency cancellation.

Entries.Name: MetadataOf
Docs: General information concerning any proposal or referendum.
The `PreimageHash` refers to the preimage of the `Preimages` provider which can be a JSON
dump or IPFS hash of a JSON file.
Consider a garbage collection for a metadata of finished referendums to `unrequest` (remove)
large preimages.

Constants.Name: EnactmentPeriod
Docs: The period between a proposal being approved and enacted.
It should generally be a little more than the unstake period to ensure that
voting stakers have an opportunity to remove themselves from the system in the case
where they are on the losing side of a vote.

Constants.Name: LaunchPeriod
Docs: How often (in blocks) new public referenda are launched.

Constants.Name: VotingPeriod
Docs: How often (in blocks) to check for new votes.

Constants.Name: VoteLockingPeriod
Docs: The minimum period of vote locking.
It should be no shorter than enactment period to ensure that in the case of an approval,
those successful voters are locked into the consequences that their votes entail.

Constants.Name: MinimumDeposit
Docs: The minimum amount to be used as a deposit for a public referendum proposal.

Constants.Name: InstantAllowed
Docs: Indicator for whether an emergency origin is even allowed to happen. Some chains may
want to set this permanently to `false`, others may want to condition it on things such
as an upgrade having happened recently.

Constants.Name: FastTrackVotingPeriod
Docs: Minimum voting period allowed for a fast-track referendum.

Constants.Name: CooloffPeriod
Docs: Period in blocks where an external proposal may not be re-submitted after being vetoed.

Constants.Name: MaxVotes
Docs: The maximum number of votes for an account.
Also used to compute weight, an overly big value can
lead to extrinsic with very big weight: see `delegate` for instance.

Constants.Name: MaxProposals
Docs: The maximum number of public proposals that can exist at any time.

Constants.Name: MaxDeposits
Docs: The maximum number of deposits a public proposal may have at any time.

Constants.Name: MaxBlacklisted
Docs: The maximum number of items which can be blacklisted.

Entries.Name: Key
Docs: The `AccountId` of the sudo key.

Entries.Name: Agenda
Docs: Items to be executed, indexed by the block number that they should be executed on.

Entries.Name: Lookup
Docs: Lookup from a name to the block number and index of the task.
For v3 -> v4 the previously unbounded identities are Blake2-256 hashed to form the v4
identities.

Constants.Name: MaximumWeight
Docs: The maximum weight that may be scheduled per block for any dispatchables.

Constants.Name: MaxScheduledPerBlock
Docs: The maximum number of scheduled calls in the queue for a single block.
NOTE:
+ Dependent pallets' benchmarks might require a higher limit for the setting. Set a
higher limit under `runtime-benchmarks` feature.

Entries.Name: IdentityOf
Docs: Information that is pertinent to identify the entity behind an account.
TWOX-NOTE: OK  `AccountId` is a secure hash.

Entries.Name: SuperOf
Docs: The super-identity of an alternative "sub" identity together with its name, within that
context. If the account is not some other account's sub-identity, then just `None`.

Entries.Name: SubsOf
Docs: Alternative "sub" identities of this account.
The first item is the deposit, the second is a vector of the accounts.
TWOX-NOTE: OK  `AccountId` is a secure hash.

Entries.Name: Registrars
Docs: The set of registrars. Not expected to get very big as can only be added through a
special origin (likely a council motion).
The index into this can be cast to `RegistrarIndex` to get a valid value.

Constants.Name: BasicDeposit
Docs: The amount held on deposit for a registered identity

Constants.Name: FieldDeposit
Docs: The amount held on deposit per additional field for a registered identity.

Constants.Name: SubAccountDeposit
Docs: The amount held on deposit for a registered subaccount. This should account for the fact
that one storage item's value will increase by the size of an account ID, and there will
be another trie item whose value is the size of an account ID plus 32 bytes.

Constants.Name: MaxSubAccounts
Docs: The maximum number of sub-accounts allowed per identified account.

Constants.Name: MaxAdditionalFields
Docs: Maximum number of additional fields that may be stored in an ID. Needed to bound the I/O
required to access an identity, but can be pretty high.

Constants.Name: MaxRegistrars
Docs: Maxmimum number of registrars allowed in the system. Needed to bound the complexity
of, e.g., updating judgements.

Entries.Name: Proxies
Docs: The set of account proxies. Maps the account which has delegated to the accounts
which are being delegated to, together with the amount held on deposit.

Entries.Name: Announcements
Docs: The announcements made by the proxy (key).

Constants.Name: ProxyDepositBase
Docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating a proxy.
This is held for an additional storage item whose value size is
`sizeof(Balance)` bytes and whose key size is `sizeof(AccountId)` bytes.

Constants.Name: ProxyDepositFactor
Docs: The amount of currency needed per proxy added.
This is held for adding 32 bytes plus an instance of `ProxyType` more into a
pre-existing storage value. Thus, when configuring `ProxyDepositFactor` one should take
into account `32 + proxy_type.encode().len()` bytes of data.

Constants.Name: MaxProxies
Docs: The maximum amount of proxies allowed for a single account.

Constants.Name: MaxPending
Docs: The maximum amount of time-delayed announcements that are allowed to be pending.

Constants.Name: AnnouncementDepositBase
Docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating an announcement.
This is held when a new storage item holding a `Balance` is created (typically 16
bytes).

Constants.Name: AnnouncementDepositFactor
Docs: The amount of currency needed per announcement made.
This is held for adding an `AccountId`, `Hash` and `BlockNumber` (typically 68 bytes)
into a pre-existing storage value.

Entries.Name: Multisigs
Docs: The set of open multisig operations.

Constants.Name: DepositBase
Docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating a multisig execution or to
store a dispatch call for later.
This is held for an additional storage item whose value size is
`4 + sizeof((BlockNumber, Balance, AccountId))` bytes and whose key size is
`32 + sizeof(AccountId)` bytes.

Constants.Name: DepositFactor
Docs: The amount of currency needed per unit threshold when creating a multisig execution.
This is held for adding 32 bytes more into a pre-existing storage value.

Constants.Name: MaxSignatories
Docs: The maximum amount of signatories allowed in the multisig.

Constants.Name: batched_calls_limit
Docs: The limit on the number of batched calls.

Entries.Name: StatusFor
Docs: The request status of a given hash.

Entries.Name: WhitelistedAccounts
Docs: List of accounts allowed to transfer free mints.
A maximum of 3 different accounts can be on the list.

Entries.Name: Seasons
Docs: Storage for the seasons.

Constants.Name: KeyLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute key.

Constants.Name: ValueLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute value.

Entries.Name: RandomMaterial
Docs: Series of block headers from the last 81 blocks that acts as random seed material. This
is arranged as a ring buffer with `block_number % 81` being the index into the `Vec` of
the oldest hash.

Entries.Name: Collection
Docs: Details of a collection.

Entries.Name: OwnershipAcceptance
Docs: The collection, if any, of which an account is willing to take ownership.

Entries.Name: Account
Docs: The items held by any given account; set out this way so that items owned by a single
account can be enumerated.

Entries.Name: CollectionAccount
Docs: The collections owned by any given account; set out this way so that collections owned by
a single account can be enumerated.

Entries.Name: CollectionRoleOf
Docs: The items in existence and their ownership details.
Stores collection roles as per account.

Entries.Name: Item
Docs: The items in existence and their ownership details.

Entries.Name: CollectionMetadataOf
Docs: Metadata of a collection.

Entries.Name: ItemMetadataOf
Docs: Metadata of an item.

Entries.Name: Attribute
Docs: Attributes of a collection.

Entries.Name: ItemPriceOf
Docs: A price of an item.

Entries.Name: ItemAttributesApprovalsOf
Docs: Item attribute approvals.

Entries.Name: NextCollectionId
Docs: Stores the `CollectionId` that is going to be used for the next collection.
This gets incremented whenever a new collection is created.

Entries.Name: PendingSwapOf
Docs: Handles all the pending swaps.

Entries.Name: CollectionConfigOf
Docs: Config of a collection.

Entries.Name: ItemConfigOf
Docs: Config of an item.

Constants.Name: CollectionDeposit
Docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved for collection.

Constants.Name: ItemDeposit
Docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved for an item.

Constants.Name: MetadataDepositBase
Docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved when adding metadata to your item.

Constants.Name: AttributeDepositBase
Docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved when adding an attribute to an item.

Constants.Name: DepositPerByte
Docs: The additional funds that must be reserved for the number of bytes store in metadata,
either "normal" metadata or attribute metadata.

Constants.Name: StringLimit
Docs: The maximum length of data stored on-chain.

Constants.Name: KeyLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute key.

Constants.Name: ValueLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute value.

Constants.Name: ApprovalsLimit
Docs: The maximum approvals an item could have.

Constants.Name: ItemAttributesApprovalsLimit
Docs: The maximum attributes approvals an item could have.

Constants.Name: MaxTips
Docs: The max number of tips a user could send.

Constants.Name: MaxDeadlineDuration
Docs: The max duration in blocks for deadlines.

Constants.Name: MaxAttributesPerCall
Docs: The max number of attributes a user could set per call.

Constants.Name: Features
Docs: Disables some of pallet's features.

Constants.Name: PalletId
Docs: The NFT-transfer's pallet id, used for deriving its sovereign account ID.

Constants.Name: KeyLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute key.

Constants.Name: ValueLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute value.

Constants.Name: PalletId
Docs: The NFT-staking's pallet id, used for deriving its sovereign account ID.

Constants.Name: MaxContracts
Docs: The maximum number of contracts an account can have.

Constants.Name: MaxStakingClauses
Docs: The maximum number of staking clauses a contract can have.

Constants.Name: MaxFeeClauses
Docs: The maximum number of fee clauses a contract can have.

Constants.Name: MaxMetadataLength
Docs: The maximum number of bytes used for a contract's metadata.

Constants.Name: KeyLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute key.

Constants.Name: ValueLimit
Docs: The maximum length of an attribute value.

Entries.Name: AccountConfig
Docs: A map of the current configuration of an account.

Entries.Name: Mogwais
Docs: A map of mogwais accessible by the mogwai hash.

Entries.Name: MogwaiPrices
Docs: A map of mogwais that are up for sale.

Entries.Name: AllMogwaisCount
Docs: A count over all existing mogwais in the system.

Entries.Name: OwnedMogwaisCount
Docs: A count over all existing mogwais owned by one account.

Entries.Name: Nonce
Docs: Nonce used for generating a different seed each time.
